Package: sTiles
Type: Package
Title: R Bindings for the sTiles Sparse Cholesky / Selected-Inverse Framework
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Esmail", "Abdul Fattah", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "esmail.abdulfattah@kaust.edu.sa")
Description: Thin R interface to the prebuilt libstiles shared library for
    tile-based sparse Cholesky factorization: log-determinants, selected
    inverse (marginal variances) and triangular solves, with symbolic reuse
    for repeated factorizations that share one sparsity pattern (e.g. INLA
    hyperparameter sweeps). The compiled glue resolves its sTiles_* symbols at
    runtime against libstiles, which is located via the STILES_LIB /
    STILES_LIB_DIR environment variables, a bundled copy under inst/libs, or a
    development checkout.
License: file LICENSE
Imports: methods, Matrix
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: libstiles shared object (libstiles.so / libstiles.dylib)
Encoding: UTF-8
